detail_description: A Nepita is a cozy restaurant in Ajaccio, offering traditional Corsican cuisine with a contemporary twist. Run by British chef Simon Andrews and his wife Roberta, the restaurant surprises diners with a different menu each day based on seasonal ingredients. The establishment is conveniently located in the city center near the peaceful Place Abbatucci. Despite being situated in a touristy area, A Nepita stands out for its authentic and high-quality Corsican dishes.
name: A NEPITA

excerpt: Formal dining room for artful contemporary dishes, plus beach tables for casual waterside meals.
detail_description: U Santa Marina is a versatile dining spot offering both formal indoor dining with artful contemporary dishes and casual beachside tables for a more relaxed experience. The restaurant provides a diverse culinary experience, featuring fresh local seafood and seasonal produce. With its beautiful terrace, U Santa Marina offers guests the opportunity to enjoy delicious meals in a picturesque seaside setting. Whether you prefer an elegant gastronomic meal or a laid-back beachside bar experience, this establishment caters to various dining preferences.
name: U Santa Marina

detail_description: Nestled on the western coast of Piana, along the stunning plage d'Arone, known for its pristine white sands and turquoise waters, is Le Café de la Plage. This beachfront restaurant exudes a relaxed atmosphere and offers upscale Mediterranean cuisine with local Corsican flavors. The rustic driftwood-style decking and furniture perfectly complement the beachside setting. Guests can unwind in warm couches or canopy beds facing the sea, making it an ideal spot for relaxation.
name: Le café de la plage
address: de la Plage d'arone, 20115 Piana, France

detail_description: Nestled along the stunning coastline of Sagone, Restaurant Le Santana is a culinary gem that promises an unforgettable dining experience. With its elegantly lit interior and charming beachside kiosk, guests can savor exquisite dishes while soaking in breathtaking views of the Gulf. The menu features delightful options such as Finger foie gras paired with Muscat Corse, succulent Blanquette of cuttlefish, and rich Scallop risotto.
name: Le Santana

detail_description: Le Piano chez Toinou is a delightful Mediterranean restaurant nestled in the vibrant town of Porticcio, just a short stroll from the beach. Known for its pristine white sandy shores and breathtaking ocean vistas, this charming spot offers an inviting atmosphere with tiled floors and rustic stone walls. Guests can enjoy their meals on a cozy covered terrace, perfect for unwinding after a day in the sun.
name: restaurant le piano chez toinou

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Bonifacio, La Bodega stands out as a gem that captures the essence of Corsican cuisine without falling into the tourist trap category. This charming eatery offers a delightful array of traditional dishes, including their popular "assiette degustation," which features an enticing selection of meats, lasagna, and local specialties like Bonifacio-style aubergine. The ambiance is inviting and cozy, making it one of the top spots for both dining and cocktails in town.
name: La Bodega

excerpt: Pizza, lobster & fish, plus cocktails & tapas, at a beachfront spot with deckchair rentals.
detail_description: Tamaricciu is a picturesque beach known for its pristine sands and clear waters, located in the southern part of Corsica. It can be reached by walking from Palombaggia beach or by following a path from the coast road. The beach offers deckchair rentals and features beachfront restaurants serving delectable dishes such as pizza, lobster, fish, and tapas along with refreshing cocktails.
name: Tamaricciu

detail_description: Playa Baggia is a popular beach restaurant located at Palombaggia beach in the south-eastern coast of Corsica. Known for its stunning views and fresh fish dishes, it's advisable to make reservations well in advance. The restaurant offers fantastic salads, including the highly recommended chicken caesar, perfect for a sunny day by the sea.
name: Playa Baggia
address: Place de Palombaggia, Lieut dit Tamaricciu, 20137 Porto-Vecchio, France

detail_description: Le Bilboq "Chez Jean-Jean" is a restaurant located at 1 Rue des Glacis, 20000 Ajaccio, France. It's known for its one-dish wonder featuring fresh-caught langouste (spiny lobster), served in the simplest and most delicious way. The restaurant is only open when the lobsters are in season and offers this delightful dish at a price of around 80 euros per person.
name: Le Bilboq "Chez jean-Jean"

detail_description: La Table de Mina in Porto-Vecchio offers an exceptional gastronomic experience by the pool, under a tiled roof, with stunning sea views. The modern Mediterranean cuisine with subtle Iberian and Italian touches delights the taste buds. The short and seasonal menu highlights exceptionally high-quality products. Situated within the luxurious Les Bergeries de Palombaggia hotel, this fine dining restaurant provides a charming outdoor dining space near the pool, offering breathtaking coastal views.
name: La Table de Mina

excerpt: Classic Corsican cuisine, sharing plates & local wines at a chalet-style space with street tables.
detail_description: Le 20123 is a charming restaurant in Ajaccio, France, offering classic Corsican cuisine served as sharing plates alongside local wines. The chalet-style space provides a cozy and inviting atmosphere for diners to enjoy their meals. With street tables available, guests can savor their dishes while taking in the surroundings. The restaurant is known for its convivial and warm ambiance, making it suitable for families with members of all ages.
name: Le 20123
address: 2 Rue Roi de Rome, 20000 Ajaccio, France

excerpt: Generous platters of raw seafood, grilled fish & pasta in a lively atmosphere with water views.
detail_description: Nestled in the old port of Bastia, Restaurant Chez Huguette is a charming spot offering a lively atmosphere and stunning water views. Specializing in delectable fish and seafood dishes like bouillabaisse, oysters, clams, and prawns, this restaurant also caters to meat lovers with options like veal and beef.
name: RESTAURANT CHEZ HUGUETTE
address: Rue de la Marine, 20200 Bastia, France

detail_description: Table de la Plage is a charming outdoor Mediterranean-style restaurant located in a stunning beachfront setting. It serves lunch from May to September and dinner during the peak summer months, offering traditional island recipes up to 4 nights a week. The ambiance is inspired by an ancient fisherman's hut, nestled among olive and mastik trees, providing both shade and sunlight.
name: Table de la Plage
address: Domaine de Murtoli Vallée de l'Ortolo, 20100 Sartène, France

detail_description: Located at 6, rue de lAssomption, Le Bistro d'Emile is a wine bar and bistro in Ajaccio that offers a relaxed and inviting atmosphere. The establishment boasts a small yet thoughtfully curated menu and an impressive variety of Corsican wines to satisfy any palate. Whether you're looking for a refreshing aperitif or some lonzu to nibble on, this place has got you covered.
name: Le Bistro d'Emile

detail_description: Auberge de la Restonica is a delightful restaurant designed like a cozy cottage, located near the charming and secluded hilltop village of Corte in central Corsica. Nestled along the banks of the Restonica river, this restaurant offers a perfect retreat for hikers and visitors seeking authentic and hearty Corsican cuisine amidst the stunning gorges and rocky landscapes. The warm and peaceful setting welcomes group lunches, while its riverside terrace provides a rare pleasure of dining in harmony with nature.
name: Auberge de la Restonica

detail_description: A Piazzetta is a rustic restaurant located in Calvi, France. Situated on a quiet square with a shady terrace, it offers a peaceful escape from the bustling tourist areas near the harbor. The restaurant is known for serving hearty and delicious French, local, and Italian cuisine at reasonable prices. Visitors praise its beautiful location, attentive staff, and incredible Corsican specialties that are simply amazing.
name: A Piazzetta

detail_description: Nestled behind a fishmonger in the charming fishing port of Saint-Florent, AUBERGE DU PECHEUR GOLFE DE LAVA is a delightful culinary gem. Owned by Damien Muller, an artisan fisherman and fishmonger, this seafood restaurant offers a menu that celebrates the best of Corsican cuisine. Diners can savor seasonal local fish and exquisite oysters sourced from nearby lagoons, complemented by fine wines from the Patrimonio region.
name: AUBERGE DU PECHEUR GOLFE DE LAVA
address: LIEU DIT LA BOCOGNANAISE - GOLFE DE LAVA, 20167 Appietto, France

detail_description: Table de la Ferme - Domaine de Murtoli offers a magical dining experience on a beautiful terrace with flawless surprise menus and perfect pairings. The exceptional service and splendid location make for an unforgettable evening. It's a place where you can discover new flavors in a chic yet relaxed atmosphere, accompanied by professional service. The young Chef of La Ferme presents great potential for the future with his mastery of flavors and textures, as well as magnificent dish presentations.
name: Table de la Ferme - Domaine de Murtoli
address: Domaine de Murtoli Vallée de l'Ortolo, 20100 Sartène, France
